# /etc/praxis/praxis-postgres.env — environment for the praxis-postgres
# container on the VPS. Copy to /etc/praxis/praxis-postgres.env and fill
# in real values. NOT committed to the repo.
#
# Wire-up: praxis-postgres.service references this file via --env-file.

POSTGRES_USER=praxis
POSTGRES_DB=praxis
# Generate a strong password on the VPS — do not commit:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=replace-me
